00:18:34.203 --> 00:18:38.269
When you re done with a phone call.
you let someone go...

234
00:18:38.270 --> 00:18:41.366
When you take someone to the airport.
you let them go...

235
00:18:41.367 --> 00:18:42.772
When you tell someone
you love her.

236
00:18:42.773 --> 00:18:46.273
and she gives you everything.
and then you go out with someone else...

237
00:18:46.373 --> 00:18:50.985
that's not letting her go.
that's dumping her. Okay? That's betrayal.

238
00:18:52.640 --> 00:18:56.731
Trevor Sheldon denied live on Hall Pass
with Robbie Mercer.

239
00:18:56.732 --> 00:18:58.532
What is your favorite scary movie. man?

240
00:18:58.593 --> 00:18:59.712
I will show you.

241
00:19:07.401 --> 00:19:11.863
Now I began to believe myself that.
that was all I was. a victim.

242
00:19:12.264 --> 00:19:14.364
And that was unacceptable to me...

243
00:19:15.079 --> 00:19:22.522
So. I sat down and began to write
a new role that would be my own.

244
00:19:22.523 --> 00:19:25.431
A role for a woman who could leave
the walls of fear behind...

245
00:19:25.432 --> 00:19:27.232
and step out into the sunlight.

246
00:19:27.332 --> 00:19:29.224
Out of Darkness.

247
00:19:30.908 --> 00:19:31.886
Thank you.

248
00:19:32.787 --> 00:19:35.135
Okay. we re gonna start
the book signing in a sec.

249
00:19:35.136 --> 00:19:37.736
so buy your copies while they last.

250
00:19:37.936 --> 00:19:40.951
<i>- May you ladies.
- New York Times best seller.</i>

251
00:19:40.952 --> 00:19:42.652
Rave reviews..

252
00:19:43.546 --> 00:19:47.522
- Gale... I am glad you came.
- Congratulations. Sidney.

253
00:19:47.822 --> 00:19:49.899
I haven't had a chance to read it yet.
but...

254
00:19:49.900 --> 00:19:51.200
Well. you can get one.

255
00:19:54.922 --> 00:20:00.286
- Dewey! Ehi!
- Hey. Sidney. Gale. you made it.

256
00:20:00.418 --> 00:20:01.563
What's going on Dewey?

257
00:20:01.564 --> 00:20:05.390
Hey. Sid. I am sorry. I gotta do
something... I am really sorry.

258
00:20:05.391 --> 00:20:07.994
Excuse me.
This will only take a minute.

259
00:20:07.995 --> 00:20:11.095
I need you all to stay where you are
and remain silent.

260
00:20:11.096 --> 00:20:13.388
Nobody leaves. you heard the Sheriff.
thank you.

261
00:20:13.389 --> 00:20:15.802
Can't this wait 45.
I'm running an event here.

262
00:20:15.803 --> 00:20:17.602
Ma'am this is a police event now.

263
00:20:17.603 --> 00:20:18.531
What's going on?

264
00:20:18.532 --> 00:20:21.813
Gale. this is police business.
If you could just let us handle this.

265
00:20:21.814 --> 00:20:23.826
I am talking to my husband. Deputy Judy.

266
00:20:23.827 --> 00:20:28.184
Listen. There's a phone we believe may have
been taken from the scene of a crime.

267
00:20:28.185 --> 00:20:31.808
Deputy Hicks has traced its location
back to these coordinates.

268
00:20:32.253 --> 00:20:35.349
- The rest is "need to know".
- And I am not "need to know"?

269
00:20:35.350 --> 00:20:36.365
Shhhh.

270
00:20:39.978 --> 00:20:41.965
Sheriff!
It's ringing out here!

271
00:20:46.132 --> 00:20:47.076
There.

272
00:20:53.108 --> 00:20:55.334
- It's coming from the trunk
- Yeah.

273
00:20:55.455 --> 00:20:57.789
- Dewey...
- They need everyone to stay back.

274
00:20:57.790 --> 00:20:59.993
- Not now. Sid.
- It's my rental.

275
00:21:09.170 --> 00:21:10.064
Damn.

276
00:21:10.065 --> 00:21:12.964
Okay. it's now official crime scene.
Let's lock it down.

277
00:21:12.965 --> 00:21:14.479
- Crime scene.
- Detach him right out of here.

278
00:21:14.480 --> 00:21:15.490
Everybody back.

279
00:21:15.491 --> 00:21:16.974
- Give me that camera.
- Stand back.

280
00:21:16.975 --> 00:21:22.256
- Please tell me this is a prank. Dewey.
- I am afraid not. Sid. Come on.

281
00:21:24.130 --> 00:21:25.619
<i>Amber. you re not gonna believe this...</i>

282
00:21:25.620 --> 00:21:28.941
- Stand back. Gale. Gale.
- Just wanna see.

283
00:21:31.941 --> 00:21:37.042
Okay. essays are due Tuesday.
"Why Woodsboro is the best"...

284
00:21:37.841 --> 00:21:41.255
Anything with an on-off swith
should be off. that's the rule.

285
00:21:42.772 --> 00:21:44.128
Somebody wanna share?

286
00:21:44.129 --> 00:21:46.380
Jenny Randall and Marnie Cooper
were murdered last night.

287
00:21:46.381 --> 00:21:47.381
What?

288
00:21:47.924 --> 00:21:50.305
- What?
- Stabbed to death.

289
00:21:50.530 --> 00:21:52.689
- What's your favorite scary movie?
- Shut up!

290
00:21:52.890 --> 00:21:57.006
- See you all Tuesday. class is not over.
- That was fast.

291
00:21:57.007 --> 00:22:00.865
This week marks the anniversary
of the infamous Woodsboro murders.

292
00:22:00.866 --> 00:22:03.160
Two girls killed the exact day...

293
00:22:03.161 --> 00:22:07.861
local celebrity victim Sidney Prescott
chose to return to her hometown.

294
00:22:07.862 --> 00:22:10.533
<i>It could be something right outta
a Gale Weathers' best seller.</i>

295
00:22:10.534 --> 00:22:12.034
<i>And where is she now?</i>

296
00:22:12.134 --> 00:22:14.073
<i>Well. living right here in Woodsboro.</i>

297
00:22:14.074 --> 00:22:16.274
<i>'cause she's the wife
of Sheriff Dewey Riley...</i>

298
00:22:16.304 --> 00:22:18.177
- First Lady.
- Perkins.

299
00:22:19.656 --> 00:22:21.741
Excuse me. Gale.
He's conducting an interview.

300
00:22:21.742 --> 00:22:23.195
Great! I love interviews.

301
00:22:23.196 --> 00:22:25.996
You have to wait. Gale.
Sorry. can't let you in there.

302
00:22:26.996 --> 00:22:29.497
What you gonna do?
Arrest me. Deputy Judy?

303
00:22:29.498 --> 00:22:32.814
If it comes to it. Civilian interference
with a police investigation...

304
00:22:32.815 --> 00:22:34.415
poses many a problem
in a court of law.

305
00:22:34.515 --> 00:22:38.726
Ok. Listen to me Judy. I don't mind
that you re working with my husband.

306
00:22:38.727 --> 00:22:42.140
Or that you re even baking
those little treats. as you do.

307
00:22:42.553 --> 00:22:44.045
But if you re gonna start
acting like him.

308
00:22:44.046 --> 00:22:46.146
you gotta put a mustache on.
'cause you sound ridiculous.

309
00:22:46.147 --> 00:22:47.111
Gale.

310
00:22:47.112 --> 00:22:48.616
- Judy.
- Gale!

311
00:22:49.854 --> 00:22:53.726
Deputy. Gale.
Calm please.

312
00:22:54.211 --> 00:22:56.730
Uh... Sidney. if you don't mind
giving us a minute.

313
00:22:56.831 --> 00:22:58.431
- Sid.
- Hi. Gale.

314
00:22:59.083 --> 00:23:02.236
Dewey. would you please explain
to Betty Crocker...

315
00:23:02.237 --> 00:23:04.137
that I have every right to be here?

316
00:23:04.503 --> 00:23:07.020
If there's been another murder
in Woodsboro obviusly...

317
00:23:08.684 --> 00:23:12.724
- That is not public information.
- It is all over the Internet. Dewey.

318
00:23:12.756 --> 00:23:13.694
It is?

319
00:23:13.695 --> 00:23:16.395
Yes. the whole world knows about it
before me.

320
00:23:16.715 --> 00:23:19.065
She wants to be a part
of the investigation. Sheriff.

321
00:23:19.707 --> 00:23:27.168
Ok. Hang on. Uhm. are you familiar with
the phrase "I wrote a book on this"?

322
00:23:30.145 --> 00:23:34.475
- Gale. with all due respect. I don't
see how that pertains to...

323
00:23:34.476 --> 00:23:36.980
Because I wrote the book on this.

324
00:23:37.590 --> 00:23:42.886
"The Woodsboro murders" by Gale Weathers.
- But you re not a reporter anymore. Gale.

325
00:23:42.887 --> 00:23:44.033
- Woah. woah. woah...
- And even if you were...

326
00:23:44.034 --> 00:23:46.744
Woah.
Don't treat me like I'm the media.

327
00:23:46.745 --> 00:23:53.193
I helped solve these things. 3 times.
remember? You and me. together.

328
00:23:53.772 --> 00:23:57.677
<i>- But I'm the Sheriff now. Gale.
- Right?</i>

329
00:23:59.843 --> 00:24:03.350
- What. you're not gonna help you with this?
- I can't.

330
00:24:05.358 --> 00:24:07.306
Alright then. I'm going.

331
00:24:07.907 --> 00:24:11.707
This is what I am good at. Dewey.
This is what I know how to do.

332
00:24:17.415 --> 00:24:19.982
Your lemon squares taste like ass.

333
00:24:22.167 --> 00:24:26.233
- They don't. They really don't.
- Thank you. Sir.

334
00:24:26.234 --> 00:24:27.809
- Sheriff.
- Yeah?

335
00:24:28.320 --> 00:24:30.133
We got a couple high school kids in here.

336
00:24:30.134 --> 00:24:33.216
2 of 'em. they say they got threatening
phone calls this morning...

337
00:24:33.217 --> 00:24:34.517
from the victims' phones.

338
00:24:34.617 --> 00:24:41.866
- Names are Olivia Morris and Jill Roberts.
- That's Sid's cousin. Damn.

339
00:24:42.689 --> 00:24:45.024
- Right in here. Sheriff.
- Hey. Jill.

340
00:24:45.025 --> 00:24:47.959
- Sidney. Hi.
- Hi.

341
00:24:48.778 --> 00:24:51.431
It's nice to see you.
even under the circumstances.

342
00:24:52.011 --> 00:24:53.798
- You okay?
- Yeah.

343
00:24:53.961 --> 00:24:55.681
So. two of you got phone calls?

344
00:24:55.782 --> 00:24:59.082
Yeah. us two.
"What's your favorite scary movie?".

345
00:24:59.529 --> 00:25:04.799
It was the killer's voice. From Stab. From.
I mean you know. from your life.

346
00:25:05.338 --> 00:25:07.687
I'm Kirby. by the way.
I'm their friend.

347
00:25:08.851 --> 00:25:11.544
- And the killer didn't call you?
- No.

348
00:25:11.816 --> 00:25:14.012
This is... this is a bad thing?

349
00:25:14.213 --> 00:25:16.613
Does that mean that I'm not gonna
live as long as these two?

350
00:25:16.713 --> 00:25:23.115
No... Maybe. Of course not.
Just. uh... just be careful.

351
00:25:23.416 --> 00:25:25.962
Oh my God. did you hear that?
I'm gonna be next!

352
00:25:25.963 --> 00:25:28.063
Dewey. I shouldn't be here.
I should leave town.

353
00:25:28.163 --> 00:25:30.781
I'm afraid
that's not really possible. Sidney.

354
00:25:30.948 --> 00:25:35.607
Look. nobody thinks you're involved.
but everyone's a suspect. I'm sorry.

355
00:25:35.608 --> 00:25:38.924
And there was evidence in your car
connecting the killer to you.

356
00:25:38.925 --> 00:25:40.625
You may be a material witness.

357
00:25:42.782 --> 00:25:46.800
So. both of you have. uh...
24 hour police protection.

358
00:25:46.801 --> 00:25:48.301
That's comforting.

359
00:25:51.166 --> 00:25:54.634
It's Rebecca.
Oh my fucking. God. Henry.

360
00:25:54.935 --> 00:25:59.836
Yes! Its true.
Two girls butchered. Pay day.

361
00:25:59.936 --> 00:26:02.039
I was so not feeling Woodsboro.

362
00:26:02.040 --> 00:26:07.640
Was like lame PR. am I right?
Well. fucking wow! Best idea ever.

363
00:26:08.346 --> 00:26:09.924
Henry. I'll call you back.

364
00:26:11.687 --> 00:26:15.276
Excuse me. I have to geek out. I didn't
got a chance to say something earlier.

365
00:26:15.277 --> 00:26:17.046
but it's such an honor
to meet you.

366
00:26:17.047 --> 00:26:18.687
- Thank you.
- Rebecca Walters.

367
00:26:18.688 --> 00:26:19.937
- Hi.
- When I was a kid...

368
00:26:19.938 --> 00:26:22.406
it was all about
top story with Gale Weathers.

369
00:26:22.407 --> 00:26:25.846
- You were my 90s!
- Well. it's Gale Riley now.

370
00:26:25.847 --> 00:26:29.225
You gave it all for love. I know that. How
long have you and Dewey been married?

371
00:26:29.226 --> 00:26:30.130
Ten years.

372
00:26:30.131 --> 00:26:33.230
Oh. just like your characters
in Stab 3. Wow!

373
00:26:33.631 --> 00:26:34.867
Wow...

374
00:26:35.974 --> 00:26:37.186
I didn't mean "bad wow".

375
00:26:37.187 --> 00:26:39.486
it's just. it always seemed like more of
a horror movie romance than a real one

376
00:26:39.487 --> 00:26:42.109
because it was a movie.
and in real life it should never be.

377
00:26:42.793 --> 00:26:47.691
Uh... dug a hole. Climbing out. here.
So anyway.

378
00:26:47.692 --> 00:26:50.187
Kudos on being brave enough
to drop off the professional map.

379
00:26:50.188 --> 00:26:52.688
Any plans
on revitalizing your tarnished brand?

380
00:26:53.647 --> 00:26:56.438
Listen. in about 2 seconds
I'm gonna revitalize your face...

381
00:26:56.439 --> 00:26:58.439
with my tarnished brand.

382
00:26:59.777 --> 00:27:00.899
I still got it.

383
00:27:02.802 --> 00:27:04.130
Uhm. tasty.

384
00:27:12.958 --> 00:27:16.292
She's so pretty. When you think about
what she survived.

385
00:27:16.293 --> 00:27:17.692
She must have scars everywhere.

386
00:27:17.693 --> 00:27:19.616
Shhhh. Come on.

387
00:27:20.029 --> 00:27:26.332
Her mom is my sister. I have scars too.
None ever asks me about my scars.

388
00:27:26.910 --> 00:27:31.066
- I am sorry Mrs. Roberts.
- She means nice scars. mom.

389
00:27:31.260 --> 00:27:34.443
Oh. well. Fine.

390
00:27:37.733 --> 00:27:45.491
- How are you? How's Gale?
- I'm alright. But Gale.

391
00:27:46.092 --> 00:27:49.407
it's been hard on her.
Small town.

392
00:27:50.308 --> 00:27:54.009
Small town husband.
Not much to write about.

393
00:27:56.213 --> 00:27:57.510
You two okay?

394
00:27:59.211 --> 00:28:04.610
Well. I read somewhere once "Just when
you think things can't get any worse.

395
00:28:05.222 --> 00:28:08.501
sometimes they don't...
sometimes. they get better".

396
00:28:09.902 --> 00:28:13.102
Out of Darkness
by Sidney Prescott. page 220.

397
00:28:22.895 --> 00:28:23.880
Gotta get going.

398
00:28:29.996 --> 00:28:33.128
It's nice to see you. Dewey.
Been through a lot together.

399
00:28:33.929 --> 00:28:36.229
We'll get through this too. okay?

400
00:28:36.884 --> 00:28:38.167
- I'll go.
- Mh-hm.

401
00:28:58.589 --> 00:29:01.893
Be good. It's okay. Relax. relax.
It's just me.

402
00:29:01.894 --> 00:29:05.240
- What the hell are you doing here?
There are cops right out front.

403
00:29:05.241 --> 00:29:06.924
No match for the ninja. baby.

404
00:29:09.445 --> 00:29:12.361
Anyway. what're you doing
in the house of Sidney Prescott?

405
00:29:12.362 --> 00:29:15.308
I mean. that's like being...
on Top Chef with Jeffrey Dahmer.

406
00:29:15.533 --> 00:29:21.293
Can you please get away from the window?
You've no right to be in here. Not anymore.

407
00:29:21.455 --> 00:29:27.134
Hang on. I heard you got a phone call
from the killer. Is that true?

408
00:29:27.817 --> 00:29:28.905
And you care?

409
00:29:30.006 --> 00:29:32.106
Don't you think it'd be a lot safer
with me around?

410
00:29:32.206 --> 00:29:34.322
I don't trust you. Trevor.

411
00:29:34.323 --> 00:29:39.030
Hey. I'm just gonna have to make sure
that you do. Alright?

412
00:29:41.990 --> 00:29:46.576
- Oh. sorry. I didn't...
- No. he's just leaving. Its... my ex.

413
00:29:46.577 --> 00:29:50.476
- Oh.
- Yeah. the one and only.

414
00:29:50.853 --> 00:29:52.503
- Hi.
- Hi.

415
00:29:53.354 --> 00:29:55.572
It's cool to meet you...
officially.

416
00:29:56.473 --> 00:29:58.973
I keep meaning to pick up a copy
of your book. but...

417
00:30:01.113 --> 00:30:02.524
You're smaller in person.

418
00:30:11.102 --> 00:30:12.050
What?

419
00:30:12.551 --> 00:30:17.352
Nothing. you just. uh...
you remind me of... me.

420
00:30:19.276 --> 00:30:22.659
- Lock your window. okay?
- Yeah. goodnight.

421
00:30:23.181 --> 00:30:24.156
Night.

422
00:30:26.659 --> 00:30:31.971
Sorry about that. Just making my rounds
before taking off.

423
00:30:31.972 --> 00:30:33.628
Great. thanks.

424
00:30:36.847 --> 00:30:40.022
- You don't remember me. do you?
- Sorry?

425
00:30:40.612 --> 00:30:43.816
We went to High School together.
Judy Hicks?

426
00:30:44.229 --> 00:30:47.677
We had the same Home-room in...
Drama club too.

427
00:30:48.378 --> 00:30:52.479
We were in Peter Pan together.
I played a Lost Boy.

428
00:30:53.479 --> 00:31:01.251
- You were... Tiger Lily.
- I'm sorry. that's a long time ago.

429
00:31:02.531 --> 00:31:08.979
It's okay. hm. You had...
a lot of stuff going on back then.

430
00:31:09.766 --> 00:31:13.847
- Well. it's nice to see you again. Judy.
- You too.

431
00:31:20.997 --> 00:31:24.389
<i>- Everything ok upstairs?
- You re supposed to be out front. Perkins.</i>

432
00:31:33.562 --> 00:31:39.770
- 4 letter word for... courage?
- Uh. guts.

433
00:31:45.282 --> 00:31:50.060
- It's Olivia Morris. she lives
next door. She's on the list.

434
00:31:50.061 --> 00:31:52.639
She can live next door to me.

435
00:31:52.978 --> 00:31:58.502
Now seriously. ehm. Mary I am warning
you. ok? I am gonna have to get physical.

436
00:31:58.503 --> 00:32:01.271
I mean it. This is it!
Just fuck off!

437
00:32:12.289 --> 00:32:14.734
- Hello?
- What are you guys up to?

438
00:32:14.792 --> 00:32:16.623
Uhm. we re watching Shaun of the Dead.

439
00:32:16.624 --> 00:32:19.733
- You know there's two zombies sitting
outside your house in a car?

440
00:32:19.734 --> 00:32:23.904
- Yeah. they are cops. You wanna come up?
- Angel of Death leave?

441
00:32:23.905 --> 00:32:28.712
- No. she's in the guest room.
- Forget it. Next door is close enough.

442
00:32:29.313 --> 00:32:32.371
- Your mom home?
- She's at her boyfriend's.

443
00:32:32.872 --> 00:32:34.773
It's creepier in here tonight.

444
00:32:34.939 --> 00:32:40.224
No. the zombies are still in their
car. so you should be alright.

445
00:32:40.225 --> 00:32:42.459
- Call me tomorrow. ok?
- Right.

446
00:32:43.144 --> 00:32:46.286
- She wanna come up?
- She fears the Reaper.

447
00:32:46.490 --> 00:32:47.715
Watch this.

448
00:32:57.169 --> 00:33:02.428
- Who's speaking?
- What's your favorite scary movie. Olivia?

449
00:33:02.664 --> 00:33:06.031
It's the worst imitation I've ever heard.
Jill. Speaking of Stab. you heard where

450
00:33:06.032 --> 00:33:07.517
the Stab- a- thon's gonna be at?

451
00:33:07.919 --> 00:33:11.134
No. It doesn't matter to me anyways.
mom doesn't let me go.

452
00:33:14.186 --> 00:33:18.227
- It's Trevor. I'll handle this.
- Trevor is calling... again.

453
00:33:18.390 --> 00:33:21.871
<i>- What do you want?
- I wanna talk to Jill.</i>

454
00:33:21.872 --> 00:33:24.333
Uh... no. it's Kirby.
Sorry. Trevor.

455
00:33:24.334 --> 00:33:27.334
Jill is screening her calls
from all past relationships.

456
00:33:27.335 --> 00:33:30.895
- What's going on over there?
- Hang on one sec. What is he saying?

457
00:33:30.985 --> 00:33:36.391
<i>- I am not Trevor.
- W... what? I can barely hear you. Trevor.</i>

458
00:33:36.762 --> 00:33:39.886
<i>- This isn't Trevor.
- Oh. oh. alright.</i>

459
00:33:39.887 --> 00:33:41.587
