that kind of attention.

685
00:52:46.757 --> 00:52:50.157
I just... feel like.
it would take over your whole life.

686
00:52:53.022 --> 00:52:57.571
Uh... all I do is I...

687
00:52:58.472 --> 00:53:00.672
try not to think about me.

688
00:53:03.073 --> 00:53:06.574
I have people I care about.
I focus on them.

689
00:53:08.101 --> 00:53:11.420
And the rest. uhm. it works out.

690
00:53:13.563 --> 00:53:19.699
You saved my life last night. I mean. I know
we're family but... you heard a thing on me.

691
00:53:20.872 --> 00:53:26.069
Makes me wonder. you know. if I'd be
brave enough to do the same thing.

692
00:53:27.931 --> 00:53:30.656
I really hope
you never have to find that out.

693
00:53:34.157 --> 00:53:37.092
Oh. if you need me.
you know where to find me.

694
00:53:37.432 --> 00:53:40.678
I'll be up in my cell. oh. I mean. my room.

695
00:54:04.947 --> 00:54:10.877
Our rooms are boarded up. That's the
view from my cell. It's really weird.

696
00:54:11.290 --> 00:54:14.912
I think Olivia would understand. okay?
She'd want me to be around other people.

697
00:54:15.638 --> 00:54:20.167
Holy shit. Even if I did just crash land
on planet dork.

698
00:54:21.550 --> 00:54:24.573
- Speaking of which. Trevor's here.
- Hey. Kirby.

699
00:54:24.574 --> 00:54:27.188
What is he doing?
That is not his scene.

700
00:54:27.189 --> 00:54:29.289
I have no idea. maybe he thought
you would be here.

701
00:54:29.619 --> 00:54:32.159
Yeah. fat chance.
After what happened last night?

702
00:54:32.160 --> 00:54:34.360
I mean. my mom is just
completely freaked out.

703
00:54:34.460 --> 00:54:35.316
It's not prim.

704
00:54:35.317 --> 00:54:39.118
Alright. you go do your good girl thing
and I'll drink for the both of us.

705
00:54:39.119 --> 00:54:42.679
- I will keep you posted.
- Alright. be safe.

706
00:55:26.752 --> 00:55:31.934
Stab-a-thon! Stab-a-thon!

707
00:55:31.935 --> 00:55:36.090
- Thank you! Thank you. Gracias. Gracias.
- Shhhh.

708
00:55:37.264 --> 00:55:40.360
Cinema Club thanks you for coming
up for our third annual Stab-a-thon.

709
00:55:40.361 --> 00:55:42.550
Thank you. number-3-thon.
We thank you in rows.

710
00:55:42.551 --> 00:55:45.147
Are you ready to drink every time
someone can't get a cellphone signal?

711
00:55:45.148 --> 00:55:46.558
Yeah!

712
00:55:46.690 --> 00:55:49.286
Are you ready to drink every time
someone shuts the refrigerator door...

713
00:55:49.287 --> 00:55:52.287
and. oh my God. there's a harmless
character right behind it?

714
00:55:52.301 --> 00:55:54.062
Yeah!

715
00:55:54.063 --> 00:55:56.328
Are you ready to drink every time
somebody screams the word...

716
00:55:56.329 --> 00:55:58.066
No!

717
00:55:58.067 --> 00:56:01.313
Let's get the Stab-athon started!

718
00:56:17.202 --> 00:56:18.780
<i>Ghostface!</i>

719
00:56:19.672 --> 00:56:21.146
<i>Get out in 5!</i>

720
00:56:22.071 --> 00:56:23.545
<i>Move your ass!</i>

721
00:56:23.989 --> 00:56:25.182
Screw you!

722
00:57:01.288 --> 00:57:02.439
Yes!

723
00:57:09.317 --> 00:57:11.595
Uh. Yeah. Back on my game.

724
00:57:13.352 --> 00:57:16.745
Perfect. New work in progress. chapter 1.

725
00:57:16.939 --> 00:57:20.654
When I moved to Woodsboro.
I never in a million years dreamed...

726
00:57:20.655 --> 00:57:23.556
that I would again
play the critical role...

727
00:57:23.656 --> 00:57:26.380
in solving another series of these...

728
00:57:34.894 --> 00:57:36.194
What the hell?

729
00:57:59.597 --> 00:58:03.367
- Gale. where are you?
- I followed the kids to the Stab-a-thon.

730
00:58:03.499 --> 00:58:06.325
There's an old abandoned farm
on 4th Dylan Road.

731
00:58:06.626 --> 00:58:08.325
Listen. I've got it under surveillance.
but...

732
00:58:08.326 --> 00:58:10.394
I think the killer is about
to make his move.

733
00:58:10.897 --> 00:58:12.465
What makes you so sure?

734
00:58:12.466 --> 00:58:16.719
You do a remake to outdo the original.
that's what the kids said.

735
00:58:16.720 --> 00:58:21.250
This party is all about the Stab movies.
Come on. how meta can you get?

736
00:58:21.590 --> 00:58:25.357
- How? "What else we get"?
- I don't know. I heard 'em say it.

737
00:58:25.625 --> 00:58:28.485
Dewey. listen to me.
you have to get out here.

738
00:58:28.486 --> 00:58:31.985
Come on. you catch the killer.
I get the story. It's a win-win.

739
00:58:31.986 --> 00:58:34.372
Well. I thought
you were going rogue. Gale.

740
00:58:34.373 --> 00:58:37.023
Oh. come...
are you serious? Come on!

741
00:58:37.909 --> 00:58:43.188
Forget it. Thanks for having faith in me!
I gotta fix my equipment.

742
00:58:43.189 --> 00:58:44.102
Gale!

743
00:58:46.668 --> 00:58:47.829
Shit.

744
00:59:03.320 --> 00:59:06.325
Bravo. well... very well done.
I'm very. very impressed.

745
00:59:07.426 --> 00:59:10.026
Kind of. Kinda impressed.
Not Really.

746
00:59:10.561 --> 00:59:11.664
- That'll do.
- Yeah?

747
00:59:11.665 --> 00:59:14.480
- Yeah. she wants you.
- Yeah. Yeah.

748
00:59:17.146 --> 00:59:19.874
<i>No... o... o... o!...</i>

749
00:59:22.163 --> 00:59:23.647
<i>Ghostface...</i>

750
00:59:32.143 --> 00:59:34.596
<i>- Hello?
- Hello.</i>

751
00:59:35.448 --> 00:59:39.631
<i>- Who is this?
- Were you expecting somebody now?</i>

752
00:59:46.824 --> 00:59:50.456
<i>You know. I don't even know you...
and I dislike you already.</i>

753
00:59:50.619 --> 00:59:52.886
Hicks. how far are you
from 4 Dylan Road?

754
00:59:52.887 --> 00:59:54.387
5 minutes at the most. Sir.

755
00:59:54.487 --> 00:59:55.599
Well. step on it.

756
00:59:57.646 --> 00:59:59.048
<i>Look out your window.</i>

757
01:00:44.374 --> 01:00:46.859
Gale! Gale. behind you!

758
01:00:59.023 --> 01:00:59.925
No!

759
01:01:03.580 --> 01:01:04.565
Gale!

760
01:01:19.973 --> 01:01:20.956
Freeze!

761
01:01:34.581 --> 01:01:36.336
Get out of the way. you morons!

762
01:01:41.713 --> 01:01:42.769
Dammit.

763
01:01:46.166 --> 01:01:49.334
- Ok. put pressure on that.
- Did you catch him?

764
01:01:49.335 --> 01:01:54.590
- No. hopefully your cameras got something.
- They weren't the only ones. Dewey.

765
01:01:54.591 --> 01:01:57.854
- What?
- There's a webcam... set back there.

766
01:01:57.855 --> 01:02:00.831
- He was watching me.
- A webcam?

767
01:02:01.129 --> 01:02:03.854
- He's recording the murders.
- What?

768
01:02:04.226 --> 01:02:07.755
This time... he's making the movie.

769
01:02:12.193 --> 01:02:16.555
This Sidney Prescott detail man.
I don't like it.

770
01:02:17.134 --> 01:02:19.403
The cops scouting the house.
they always get it.

771
01:02:20.618 --> 01:02:23.301
What are you talking about?
- It's a movie cop rule.

772
01:02:23.568 --> 01:02:27.298
Sucks to be a cop in a movie.
Unless you re Bruce Willis.

773
01:02:27.299 --> 01:02:29.359
Not all cops die in movies.

774
01:02:29.836 --> 01:02:33.532
No. but if it's your last day
before retirement you do.

775
01:02:34.185 --> 01:02:37.119
If you re a rookie. some with a
wife who's pregnant. you do.

776
01:02:38.502 --> 01:02:40.049
Or if your partner
is better looking than you.

777
01:02:40.050 --> 01:02:42.950
you do. and by the way.
I win that one.

778
01:02:44.799 --> 01:02:47.766
You know what. I'll take the next
perimeter. I'll be right back.

779
01:02:49.983 --> 01:02:51.074
Shit.

780
01:02:51.675 --> 01:02:54.261
I know this one. you're not
supposed to say that. are you?

781
01:02:54.262 --> 01:02:55.862
Eh. new decade. new rules.

782
01:02:55.863 --> 01:03:00.142
You know. these days. you might come back.
find me dead. Eyes gouged out. tongue

783
01:03:00.143 --> 01:03:01.983
sticking out. Could go either way.

784
01:03:01.984 --> 01:03:05.856
- I gotta learn this shit.
- Eh. I'll take this one.

785
01:03:08.136 --> 01:03:13.479
- Hey. Hoss. Be careful.
- I'm always careful.

786
01:03:17.260 --> 01:03:19.078
Dead man walking.

787
01:04:09.199 --> 01:04:11.863
Perkins. was there a window open
on your last perimeter check?

788
01:04:15.365 --> 01:04:17.065
Perkins. come in. Over.

789
01:04:47.645 --> 01:04:48.584
Anthony?

790
01:04:50.431 --> 01:04:51.402
Perkins?

791
01:04:56.724 --> 01:04:57.941
Damn it.

792
01:04:57.942 --> 01:05:00.742
You should've seen the look
on your face. rookie.

793
01:05:02.817 --> 01:05:04.991
Hoss! What the fuck!

794
01:05:06.956 --> 01:05:08.149
Holy shit...

795
01:05:18.751 --> 01:05:19.704
Hoss!

796
01:05:36.602 --> 01:05:37.898
Fuck Bruce Willis!

797
01:06:07.008 --> 01:06:12.550
- Sorry. The wind chimes were over here.
- It was me. I was trying to fix em. sorry.

798
01:06:14.288 --> 01:06:17.493
- I am just back the store.
- Were you shopping?

799
01:06:17.656 --> 01:06:21.943
A stress buster. I got one more bag
in the car. I'll be right back.

800
01:06:48.135 --> 01:06:49.681
Jill. you re gonna get that?

801
01:06:53.944 --> 01:06:57.216
<i>- Roberts residence.
- You re a survivor. aren't you. Sidney?</i>

802
01:06:57.217 --> 01:07:02.758
<i>Your one and only skill: You survive.
Well. I have one question for you.</i>

803
01:07:03.233 --> 01:07:05.840
<i>What good it to be a survivor
in this little drama...</i>

804
01:07:05.841 --> 01:07:07.941
<i>if everyone close to you
is dead?</i>

805
01:07:08.312 --> 01:07:11.303
<i>- Who are you?
- Turn on the TV to channel 6.</i>

806
01:07:11.304 --> 01:07:14.907
<i>- Who the fuck are you?
- Turn it on. Watch the teaser.</i>

807
01:07:16.665 --> 01:07:20.816
<i>But it nearly turned deadly tonight. with
the latest victim of this attack being</i>

808
01:07:20.817 --> 01:07:22.649
<i>the wife of the Woodsboro Sheriff...</i>

809
01:07:22.650 --> 01:07:25.456
<i>Gale Riley. aka Gale Weathers.</i>

810
01:07:25.457 --> 01:07:28.057
<i>who's in serious condition tonight
after being stabbed.</i>

811
01:07:28.058 --> 01:07:29.854
<i>Her assailant then disappeared...</i>

812
01:07:29.855 --> 01:07:33.733
<i>- in a sea of identity...
- Glad you came home. Sidney.</i>

813
01:07:33.734 --> 01:07:34.984
Has it been worth it yet?

814
01:07:35.034 --> 01:07:36.818
Why are you doing this?

815
01:07:36.819 --> 01:07:42.141
Ah. friends count. but it's the family
ties that cut deep. Am I right?

816
01:07:42.660 --> 01:07:44.019
What do you mean?

817
01:07:44.020 --> 01:07:48.290
- The ones you care about most.
And what's closer than family?

818
01:07:48.291 --> 01:07:50.286
<i>- The bond of blood.
- Don't.</i>

819
01:07:50.626 --> 01:07:54.709
<i>You can't save them.
All you can do is watch.</i>

820
01:07:56.018 --> 01:07:56.929
Jill!

821
01:08:15.611 --> 01:08:17.340
- Kate!
- Sid?

822
01:08:17.341 --> 01:08:19.363
- She's not in her room.
- Oh my God.

823
01:08:19.364 --> 01:08:21.384
She's gone at Kirby's. You gotta
call her. get her back here.

824
01:08:21.385 --> 01:08:22.305
Okay.

825
01:08:24.025 --> 01:08:25.990
<i>- Come on. Jill!
- Leave a message.</i>

826
01:08:26.216 --> 01:08:28.345
She's not picking up.
What's going on?

827
01:08:28.346 --> 01:08:32.096
- The killer called. he's coming after
me. But he wants my family first.

828
01:08:32.097 --> 01:08:33.957
- Oh God. Jill...
- Let's get the cops.

829
01:08:34.568 --> 01:08:35.792
- The cops aren't there.
- What?

830
01:08:35.893 --> 01:08:38.266
They were there when I first came
in. but they re not there now.

831
01:08:38.267 --> 01:08:39.274
Let's get to Kirby's.

832
01:08:43.473 --> 01:08:44.603
Out the front.

833
01:08:53.075 --> 01:08:55.592
Press up on the bottom. Can you?

834
01:09:01.877 --> 01:09:02.860
Let's get out of here.

835
01:09:04.182 --> 01:09:06.897
Kate. come on! Kate!

836
01:09:18.477 --> 01:09:23.186
- Tell Jill I am so sorry...
- No. no. no. no. shhhh...

837
01:09:34.442 --> 01:09:35.437
Kate...

838
01:09:52.012 --> 01:09:53.356
Hicks.
What're you doing?

839
01:09:53.357 --> 01:09:56.087
I just saw somebody coming
around the side of the house.

840
01:09:56.088 --> 01:09:58.146
Where are Hoss and Perkins?
I couldn't get 'em on the radio.

841
01:09:59.677 --> 01:10:00.825
Whose blood is that?

842
01:10:01.326 --> 01:10:04.926
It's... It's Kate's.
we were just attacked. She's dead.

843
01:10:05.026 --> 01:10:07.333
- Where is she?
- The front door.

844
01:10:07.673 --> 01:10:09.107
- Show me.
- Okay.

845
01:10:13.868 --> 01:10:15.030
- Stay here.
- Okay.

846
01:10:21.178 --> 01:10:25.182
This is Deputy Hicks. I've got a homicide
at the Roberts' residence.

847
01:10:25.183 --> 01:10:26.884
No sign of Perkins or Hoss.

848
01:10:27.050 --> 01:10:29.943
- Copy that. We'll try to locate 'em.
- I'm so sorry.

849
01:10:41.324 --> 01:10:44.170
You're gonna be fine. alright?
I swear.

850
01:10:44.871 --> 01:10:48.371
No more on your own.
It's you and me. forever.

851
01:10:50.396 --> 01:10:51.274
Easy.

852
01:10:52.867 --> 01:10:54.444
- Dewey.
- Yeah?

853
01:10:56.734 --> 01:10:59.105
Promise me something.
- Anything.

854
01:11:00.167 --> 01:11:05.568
- Catch that motherfucker.
- Absolutely. I love you.

855
01:11:05.569 --> 01:11:06.626
I love you.

856
01:11:09.123 --> 01:11:13.398
- It was chaos. Utter chaos.
- I can't believe that.

857
01:11:13.699 --> 01:11:17.220
The Sheriff's wife. man. She told us
to cancel it and we didn't and now this?

858
01:11:17.221 --> 01:11:18.120
What're we supposed to do. huh?

859
01:11:18.121 --> 01:11:20.150
Robbie. calm down. It makes sense.

860
01:11:20.217 --> 01:11:23.048
This is about the reboots too.
They. they. they one up the original ending.

861
01:11:23.210 --> 01:11:26.648
"The Woodsboro murders" ended
at a party. so in the remake...

862
01:11:26.649 --> 01:11:29.200
The party is the false ending.
New rules.

863
01:11:29.332 --> 01:11:30.735
Exactly.

864
01:11:31.536 --> 01:11:33.536
Okay. no offense guys
but I'm gonna put in Stab 7.

865
01:11:33.636 --> 01:11:35.258
- Yes...
- Nobody cancels my film festival.

866
01:11:35.389 --> 01:11:39.130
Whoa. I don't wanna watch that.
Not after what happened to Olivia.

867
01:11:39.131 --> 01:11:41.061
Oh. come on.
It was her favorite.

868
01:11:41.062 --> 01:11:44.881
Oh. wow Kirby. You have some classics here.
- Yup.

869
01:11:44.882 --> 01:11:46.571
"Suspiria"."Don't look now"...

870
01:11:46.572 --> 01:11:50.520
You know it. I can trivia your ass
under the table. cinema boy.

871
01:11:50.521 --> 01:11:54.763
Oh. yeah? Who played Leatherface first?
- Gunnar Hansen.

872
01:11:54.764 --> 01:11:57.802
Wow. did you feel that?

873
01:11:59.185 --> 01:12:04.102
- The charge that moved between us. then?
- Oh. that was me. I have powers.

874
01:12:04.265 --> 01:12:05.706
So sexy...

875
01:12:06.631 --> 01:12:09.254
You guys are unbelievable.
You're playing fucking trivia games?

876
01:12:09.255 --> 01:12:10.654
The cops are gonna come for us.

877
01:12:10.655 --> 01:12:11.853
they're gonna shut down my website.

878
01:12:11.854 --> 01:12:14.209
- We're so dead!
- Yeah. I agree.

879
01:12:14.210 --> 01:12:16.014
Jesus Christ. where did you come from?

880
01:12:16.015 --> 01:12:19.608
The front door. By the way Kirby. with
everything that's going on right now...

881
01:12:19.609 --> 01:12:21.530
you probably
shouldn't leave that unlocked.

882
01:12:22.931 --> 01:12:24.131
Sorry...

883
01:12:24.379 --> 01:12:27.659
And. uh... may I ask.
what the hell you're doing here?

884
01:12:27.660 --> 01:12:30.260
What?
Didn't I find the After-party?

885
01:12:30.468 --> 01:12:33.398
No. you found the Anti-party
and it's invitation only.

886
01:12:33.399 --> 01:12:36.800
Yeah. well. I got an invitation...
from Jill.

887
01:12:38.706 --> 01:12:42.723
So. what's the story?
- What?

888
01:12:43.167 --> 01:12:46.692
You sent me a text message.
After-party at Kirby's house.

889
01:12:47.394 --> 01:12:49.094
I mean. it's from your phone.

890
01:12:49.194 --> 01:12:51.076
What do you mean.
from my phone?

891
01:12:51.777 --> 01:12:56.877
Oh. where is my phone? I think I left it
in your car. I didn't text him.

892
01:12:57.079 --> 01:13:01.093
I didn't text you.
I'll prove it!

893
01:13:02.751 --> 01:13:08.084
So. Charlie. Robbie. how does it feel
to be accessories to a crime. huh?

894
01:13:08.320 --> 01:13:12.087
- I mean. really? Dewey's wife?
- My life is over.

895
01:13:12.146 --> 01:13:15.049
So which one of you guys sent me
a text message from Jill's phone. huh?

896
01:13:17.983 --> 01:13:21.143
W... we're supposed to accept
that you re telling the truth?

897
01:13:21.144 --> 01:13:23.064
Isn't your phone missing?

898
01:13:23.835 --> 01:13:28.157
- Got a new one.
- Really? Oh. that's incredibly convenient.

899
01:13:29.895 --> 01:13:31.889
Dewey. it's Hicks.
- What's up?

900
01:13:32.845 --> 01:13:34.449
- Kate Roberts is dead.
- Huh?

901
01:13:34.450 --> 01:13:38.741
- And Sidney fled the scene.
- What. what happened to Kate?

902
01:13:39.112 --> 01:13:41.901
- She was stabbed. just like the others.
- And what about Jill?

903
01:13:42.178 --> 01:13:45.873
- No sign of her at all
- Where the hell were Hoss and Perkins?

904
01:13:46.349 --> 01:13:51.817
<i>They were found dead in their car
2 blocks away. Multiple stab wounds.</i>

905
01:13:52.679 --> 01:13:57.489
<i>Ok. I'm on my way.
- Yes. Sir.</i>

906
01:14:05.243 --> 01:14:08.074
<i>- Wrong number.
- Who was that?</i>

907
01:14:08.476 --> 01:14:10.576
<i>- Oh. nobody.
- Did you pick a movie?</i>

908
01:14:10.874 --> 01:14:16.128
<i>- Yeah. we re gonna go scary: Saw IV.
- Oh. I saw that in theaters. It sucks.</i>

909
01:14:16.129 --> 01:14:19.539
<i>It's not scary. it's gross.
I hate all that torture porn shit.</i>

910
01:14:19.540 --> 01:14:21.639
<i>How do you really feel.</i>

911
01:14:22.563 --> 01:14:26.151
<i>Well. I like Jigsaw. I think
he kills people very creatively.</i>

912
01:14:26.152 --> 01:14:28.338
<i>But she don't give a shit who dies...</i>

913
01:14:28.339 --> 01:14:30.030
<i>cause there's no character
to fill a man.</i>

914
01:14:30.031 --> 01:14:32.531
<i>It's just body parts whipping
and blood spewing...</i>

915
01:14:43.094 --> 01:14:45.892
Charlie. you wanna sit next to me?

916
01:14:53.710 --> 01:15:00.236
Alright... Get ready for a Hall Pass
with Robbie Mercer extra. Now tonight.

917
01:15:00.237 --> 01:15:03.490
there is a good chance
that Charlie Walker...

918
01:15:03.522 --> 01:15:07.796
yes. my Charlie Walker.
may get lucky with a girl.

919
01:15:08.898 --> 01:15:11.898
Now I'm unable to...
publish my exact location.

920
01:15:11.998 --> 01:15:15.388
however. suffice it to say...

921
01:15:15.555 --> 01:15:21.547
Woodsboro High may be in store
for some geek history. We'll see.

922
01:15:35.265 --> 01:15:36.582
Hello?

923
01:15:39.810 --> 01:15:41.106
Who's there?

924
01:15:46.451 --> 01:15:48.374
Oh my God.

925
01:16:02.218 --> 01:16:05.152
<i>- Where are you going?
- To make sure the front door is locked.</i>

926
01:16:07.431 --> 01:16:10.545
<i>- No. don't open it.
- You're overreacting.</i>

927
01:16:13.241 --> 01:16:14.403
- Hey. Charlie.
- Yeah?

928
01:16:16.338 --> 01:16:19.698
I'm sorry. I know you're into the movie
and all. but...

929
01:16:20.199 --> 01:16:23.199
now would be a really good time
to make a move.

930
01:16:24.449 --> 01:16:28.072
- For me to make a move?
- Mh-hm.

931
01:16:30.259 --> 01:16:33.609
- Couldn't you make a move?
- I just did.

932
01:16:35.054 --> 01:16:37.196
'Cause you're actually pretty cute.

933
01:16:38.198 --> 01:16:43.498
Especially when I'm scared...
and lonely... and drunk...

934
01:16:46.440 --> 01:16:51.891
Hey. guys. Did... did you see Jill. come in?
I didn't see her outside.

935
01:16:51.892 --> 01:16:54.558
Yes. Trevor. She is upstairs.

936
01:16:54.930 --> 01:16:58.072
Thank God you're here to protect her.
when you can't even find her.

937
01:16:58.996 --> 01:17:00.971
There's nobody out here.

938
01:17:00.972 --> 01:17:03.496
Oh. dude.
I love this part of the movie.

939
01:17:03.497 --> 01:17:06.072
- Yeah. yeah.
- What'd he say?

940
01:17:06.073 --> 01:17:09.999
Just when you think they're all safe
and comfortable in the house...

941
01:17:10.339 --> 01:17:12.816
Ghostface comes in and bang!

942
01:17:16.731 --> 01:17:18.677
Did I interrupt something for you?

943
01:17:19.578 --> 01:17:25.578
- Shut the fuck up.
- Who invited you. Trevor?

944
01:17:25.648 --> 01:17:30.034
Alright. Clearly not you.
Wow.

945
01:17:30.205 --> 01:17:35.225
- I'm moving upstairs.
- Get out of my house!

946
01:17:38.037 --> 01:17:43.963
Ehi. okay. I'm a little drunk. so...
don't blame your Internet connection.

947
01:17:45.169 --> 01:17:50.710
Let's see what Charlie is up to. shall we?
Or the saga of Trevor and Jill...

948
01:17:50.945 --> 01:17:55.162
Oh. intrigue of Woodsboro High.
Who needs to kill around with so much drama?

949
01:18:09.694 --> 01:18:11.241
Oh. man...

950
01:18:12.967 --> 01:18:15.903
Yeah... That's better.

951
01:18:29.974 --> 01:18:33.007
Wait. no! You can't.
you can't. there's rules.

952
01:18:33.008 --> 01:18:37.571
I... I... I'm gay. I'm gay.
I mean. if it helps...

953
01:18:44.552 --> 01:18:47.794
<i>...some random girl who gets a call that
undoubtedly ends up getting her killed.</i>

954
01:18:47.795 --> 01:18:51.627
<i>It's all so predictable. There's no element
of surprise. You can see ev...</i>

955
01:19:06.542 --> 01:19:09.653
Kirby! So. my phone was up in your room.

956
01:19:09.654 --> 01:19:13.455
There was no text message
sent to Trevor. He is such a liar.

957
01:19:14.610 --> 01:19:15.628
Where is he?

958
01:19:16.129 --> 01:19:19.160
What do you mean. where is he.
he just went upstairs looking for you.

959
01:19:19.453 --> 01:19:21.542
He's not upstairs.

960
01:19:22.843 --> 01:19:28.544
Trevor!...
Charlie! Robbie!

961
01:19:29.506 --> 01:19:30.844
Maybe they are outside.

962
01:19:32.354 --> 01:19:33.491
- Jill.
- Sidney!

963
01:19:33.592 --> 01:19:35.791
I... I'm sorry.
I should have told you about...

964
01:19:35.792 --> 01:19:37.264
No. it's okay.
I need you to come with me.

965
01:19:37.265 --> 01:19:40.504
Come with me right now. okay?
Run!

966
01:19:42.136 --> 01:19:43.248
Robbie!

967
01:19:46.654 --> 01:19:47.594
Go!

968
01:19:50.658 --> 01:19:51.684
Sidney!

969
01:19:53.790 --> 01:19:54.948
Come on!

970
01:19:58.670 --> 01:20:01.002
- The balcony!
- There's no other way out?

971
01:20:01.173 --> 01:20:02.555
We can jump?

972
01:20:04.157 --> 01:20:06.612
It's two stories.
Where's your cell?

973
01:20:07.113 --> 01:20:08.295
- Get under the bed.
- What?

974
01:20:08.296 --> 01:20:09.946
Just do what I say. Get under the bed
and don't make a sound...

975
01:20:09.947 --> 01:20:11.347
and don't come out
'till I come get you.

976
01:20:11.447 --> 01:20:13.712
- Just go. Trust me!
- Okay.

977
01:20:20.894 --> 01:20:24.562
You got it? You okay? Jill. run.
Just keep running. Get out!

978
01:20:50.652 --> 01:20:51.860
- Hello?
- Dewey!

979
01:20:51.861 --> 01:20:54.164
- Sidney. where are you?
- I'm at Kirby's.

980
01:20:54.165 --> 01:20:55.865
The killer is here. I need your help.

981
01:20:55.866 --> 01:20:57.821
- I'm on my way.
- Okay.

982
01:21:00.600 --> 01:21:02.374
Sid!
Sidney!

983
01:21:02.712 --> 01:21:07.792
- I need all units to 329 Whispering Lane.
- All units! 329 Whispering Lane!

984
01:21:28.464 --> 01:21:31.573
Sorry. it's just me. Look. I tried to call
911 with the land line instead.

985
01:21:31.574 --> 01:21:32.673
but someone smashed the router.

986
01:21:32.674 --> 01:21:35.252
- I think I called them myself.
- Well. where's Jill?

987
01:21:36.189 --> 01:21:38.392
Go. go. go. go!

988
01:21:42.382 --> 01:21:44.868
There's a room down there.
We can lock ourselves in.

989
01:21:45.166 --> 01:21:47.449
I heard you yelling to Jill.
Did she get away?

990
01:21:47.450 --> 01:21:48.950
I think she's safe.

991
01:21:56.615 --> 01:21:59.165
- Kirby. let me in!
- Charlie...

992
01:22:01.591 --> 01:22:04.288
No. no. no. no. no. don't.
I just found Robbie.

993
01:22:04.489 --> 01:22:06.089
It's... it's just his blood. please.

994
01:22:06.178 --> 01:22:09.041
Please. there is someone else out here.
Let me in.

995
01:22:09.042 --> 01:22:10.842
If you can't trust him.
don't open the door.

996
01:22:12.372 --> 01:22:15.692
- My God! Let me in!
- Get away from the door. Charlie.

997
01:22:15.990 --> 01:22:19.888
- Kirby. it's me! Please let me in!
- Get away from the door. Charlie!

998
01:22:19.889 --> 01:22:25.192
- It's me!
- I'm sorry. I can't...

999
01:22:25.323 --> 01:22:28.288
What the fuck...
- I am sorry.

1000
01:22:29.077 --> 01:22:30.508
Behind you! Look out!

1001
01:22:33.112 --> 01:22:35.451
No. no. no. no. no!

1002
01:22:37.178 --> 01:22:38.383
Kirby!

1003
01:22:48.774 --> 01:22:52.053
Oh. no. God. no. He's...
Leave him alone!

1004
01:22:52.872 --> 01:22:54.419
Leave him alone!

1005
01:22:57.575 --> 01:22:59.497
It's Charlie's phone.

1006
01:23:00.998 --> 01:23:05.780
Tell Sidney heads are gonna roll tonight.
Tell Sidney it's all because of her.

1007
01:23:05.781 --> 01:23:10.538
Or maybe she wants into his place.
I promise to be quick.

1008
01:23:10.939 --> 01:23:12.825
- It's him.
- Okay. I'm gonna get Jill.

1009
01:23:12.826 --> 01:23:13.956
She should be in the same place.

1010
01:23:13.957 --> 01:23:16.458
Just keep him on the phone.
I'll be right back. okay?

1011
01:23:19.139 --> 01:23:20.661
Let him go. please...

1012
01:23:20.662 --> 01:23:25.483
<i>I hear you like horror movies. Kirby.
But do you like 'em as much as him?</i>

1013
01:23:25.792 --> 01:23:29.333
<i>Forget watching Stab.
You get to live it.</i>

1014
01:23:29.434 --> 01:23:32.534
No. no. no. no. no.
He's the expert. it's not me.

1015
01:23:32.634 --> 01:23:37.189
<i>- Warm up question: Jason's weapon?
- Uh... it's a machete.</i>

1016
01:23:37.190 --> 01:23:41.502
There. you see? You do know
the genre. Michael Mayers?

1017
01:23:41.503 --> 01:23:43.352
Uh... butcher knife.

1018
01:23:43.353 --> 01:23:46.236
<i>- Leatherface?
- A chainsaw. Please...</i>

1019
01:23:46.237 --> 01:23:48.483
Just ask Sidney if you need some help.
Freddy Krueger?

1020
01:23:48.484 --> 01:23:50.130
Uh... uh... razor hands.

1021
01:23:50.131 --> 01:23:52.465
Name the movie
that started the slasher craze:

1022
01:23:52.466 --> 01:23:54.165
"Halloween".
"the Texas Chainsaw Massacre".

1023
01:23:54.166 --> 01:23:56.676
<i>- "The Last House on the Left" or "Psycho"?
- "Psycho".</i>

1024
01:23:56.767 --> 01:24:00.681
<i>None of the above. "Peeping Tom". 1960.
directed by Michael Powell.</i>

1025
01:24:00.682 --> 01:24:04.506
<i>First movie to ever put
the audience in the killer's POV.</i>

1026
01:24:05.207 --> 01:24:06.395
Wait.
No. no. no.

1027
01:24:06.396 --> 01:24:08.987
Please. just ask me
one more question. just one more.

1028
01:24:09.388 --> 01:24:14.466
<i>Alright. Kirby. Then it's time
for your last chance question.</i>

1029
01:24:15.267 --> 01:24:19.603
<i>Name the remake of the groundbreaking
horror movie in which the villain...</i>

1030
01:24:19.604 --> 01:24:23.789
"Halloween". "Texas Chainsaw".
"Dawn of the Dead". "The Hills Have Eyes".

1031
01:24:23.790 --> 01:24:26.328
"The Amityville Horror".
"The Last House on the Left"

1032
01:24:26.329 --> 01:24:30.097
"Friday the 13th". "A Nightmare
on Elm Street". "My Bloody Valentine".

1033
01:24:30.098 --> 01:24:34.298
"When a Stranger Calls". "Prom Night".
"Black Christmas". "House of Wax".

1034
01:24:34.299 --> 01:24:39.968
"The Fog". uh... "Piranha".
It's one of those. right? Right?!

1035
01:24:47.449 --> 01:24:50.978
I got it right. I was fucking right!

1036
01:24:51.099 --> 01:24:52.021
Jill?

1037
01:25:04.394 --> 01:25:09.554
I won. Charlie. I fucking won. I won.
He tried to beat me. but I fucking won.

1038
01:25:09.555 --> 01:25:10.945
It's so great...

1039
01:25:14.936 --> 01:25:22.708
- Wait. I'm almost there. Just hang tight.
- Kirby? He's making a move.

1040
01:25:26.240 --> 01:25:29.184
Four years of classes together
and you notice me now?

1041
01:25:29.885 --> 01:25:32.685
You stupid bitch!
It's too late!

1042
01:25:34.247 --> 01:25:39.525
Shh. shhhh. I know. I know.
It's okay. take your time.

1043
01:25:39.526 --> 01:25:43.318
Doesn't happen as fast
as it does in the movies. honey.

1044
01:25:43.519 --> 01:25:44.476
Charlie...

1045
01:26:11.438 --> 01:26:12.522
Kirby?

1046
01:26:17.192 --> 01:26:19.517
You know. you learn the law
when you watch movies over and over.

1047
01:26:19.857 --> 01:26:22.084
All the plots are about trying to kill you.

1048
01:26:23.855 --> 01:26:24.844
Where's Jill?

1049
01:26:24.845 --> 01:26:28.329
Oh. you think she's gonna get away?
You think anyone gets away?

1050
01:26:38.678 --> 01:26:42.938
- Jill?
- Hello. Sidney. Surprised?

1051
01:26:43.653 --> 01:26:51.320
Watch this. This is the part when. dear
cousin. the cameras... turn off.

1052
01:26:55.279 --> 01:26:57.754
- Charlie?
- Want her taken care of.

1053
01:26:58.271 --> 01:27:00.974
Then I got great footage
in my Robbie kill.

1054
01:27:00.975 --> 01:27:03.175
Better than Jenny and Marnie
and Olivia even.

1055
01:27:03.575 --> 01:27:06.309
Good. We'll cut and upload it later.
Make it all traceable to Trevor.

1056
01:27:06.310 --> 01:27:12.741
Speaking of which...
Remind you of anything?

1057
01:27:12.881 --> 01:27:15.446
- Jill. please...
- Shut up! Dick.

1058
01:27:15.447 --> 01:27:17.281
Everything I learned.
I learned from you.

1059
01:27:17.882 --> 01:27:20.183
You think you had a shitty boyfriend.
Sidney?

1060
01:27:20.283 --> 01:27:25.812
Here's one that fucks you. dumps you
and doesn't even make you famous.

1061
01:27:25.813 --> 01:27:28.749
What the fuck. Jill.
I loved you!

1062
01:27:28.750 --> 01:27:31.164
Shut the fuck up. already!

1063
01:27:33.934 --> 01:27:36.930
Sure those cops wanted you
to have this. Jill. For your protection.

1064
01:27:38.033 --> 01:27:39.118
Put it down...

1065
01:27:40.408 --> 01:27:41.433
Please...

1066
01:27:44.034 --> 01:27:45.914
Shouldn't have killed
all those people. Trev.

1067
01:27:46.415 --> 01:27:48.215
Gone and put it on video even.

1068
01:27:48.606 --> 01:27:52.932
- But it means a lot that you did it for me.
- What the fuck are you talking about?

1069
01:27:52.933 --> 01:27:56.207
I am not! The girl
you cheat on.

1070
01:28:01.275 --> 01:28:04.817
- I've gone thru everything. We're
definitely good on timeline.

1071
01:28:04.818 --> 01:28:06.288
Oh. yeah.
We're perfect.

1072
01:28:06.289 --> 01:28:08.077
No. no. no. Please.

1073
01:28:15.403 --> 01:28:16.878
Ready for act 3?

1074
01:28:18.187 --> 01:28:19.586
Have you figured it out yet. Sidney?

1075
01:28:20.287 --> 01:28:24.288
Keeping it to our remake theme.
Trevor is this generation's Billy Loomis...

1076
01:28:24.308 --> 01:28:27.556
and we're the innocent victims:
Sidney and Randy.

1077
01:28:27.988 --> 01:28:31.462
See. with you. the world
just heard about what happened...

1078
01:28:31.463 --> 01:28:34.263
but with us.
they're gonna see it.

1079
01:28:34.363 --> 01:28:36.133
It's gonna be a worldwide sensation.

1080
01:28:36.134 --> 01:28:40.635
And people gotta see this shit.
It's not like anyone reads anymore.

1081
01:28:42.963 --> 01:28:47.702
I gonna know fame
like you never even dreamed of.

1082
01:28:48.354 --> 01:28:50.317
Last two teenagers standing.

1083
01:28:51.318 --> 01:28:53.218
This time Randy gets the girl.

1084
01:28:58.919 --> 01:29:01.919
You're amazing.
And you're the perfect victim.

1085
01:29:02.129 --> 01:29:06.066
I was so believable today. wasn't I?
I mean.

1086
01:29:06.067 --> 01:29:09.367
I told so many lies.
I actually started to believe them.

1087
01:29:10.167 --> 01:29:12.318
I really think
that I was born for this.

1088
01:29:12.319 --> 01:29:14.186
How could you do this?

1089
01:29:14.187 --> 01:29:19.014
Do you know what it was like
growing up in this family?

1090
01:29:19.416 --> 01:29:23.335
Related to you?
I mean. all I ever heard was:

1091
01:29:23.436 --> 01:29:27.336
Sidney this and Sidney that.
and Sidney. Sidney. Sidney.

1092
01:29:27.835 --> 01:29:32.948
You were always so fucking special!
Well. now I'm the special one.

1093
01:29:33.549 --> 01:29:35.607
You'll slip. they always do.

1094
01:29:36.645 --> 01:29:44.310
Come on. Charlie. Let's go on with this.
You have to be strong and hold still. Ok?

1095
01:29:44.311 --> 01:29:51.757
Yeah. yeah. old school. like Billy and Stu.
Come on. baby. get it up. Come on.

1096
01:29:52.691 --> 01:29:55.376
Shoulder me. shoulder me. shoulder me.
Get it up!

1097
01:30:01.628 --> 01:30:03.295
Not the way we rehearsed it.

1098
01:30:03.296 --> 01:30:06.794
You said it. Charlie:
Billy and Stu. Trevor and you.

1099
01:30:08.000 --> 01:30:12.754
What the media really loves. baby.
is a sole survivor.

1100
01:30:13.155 --> 01:30:16.755
Just ask you know who.
Trevor was your partner...

1101
01:30:17.255 --> 01:30:20.147
and you.
you were the idea man.

1102
01:30:30.180 --> 01:30:31.656
Even your friends?

1103
01:30:32.858 --> 01:30:37.893
My friends? What world
are you living in? I don't need friends.

1104
01:30:38.694 --> 01:30:40.194
I need fans.

1105
01:30:40.773 --> 01:30:42.650
Don't you get it?!

1106
01:30:42.651 --> 01:30:48.852
This has never been about killing you.
It's about... becoming you.

1107
01:30:49.456 --> 01:30:51.813
I mean. for fuck's sake.
my own mother had to die.

1108
01:30:51.814 --> 01:30:55.014
no great loss there.
so I could stay true. to the original.

1109
01:30:55.726 --> 01:31:00.598
It's sick. right?
Well sick. is the new sane.

1110
01:31:01.699 --> 01:31:04.399
You had your 15 minutes.
now I want mine!

1111
01:31:05.358 --> 01:31:06.741
I mean. what am I supposed to do?

1112
01:31:06.742 --> 01:31:11.943
Go to college. grad school. work?
Look around.

1113
01:31:12.243 --> 01:31:15.028
we all live in public now.
we're all on the Internet.

1114
01:31:15.029 --> 01:31:17.402
How do you think
people become famous anymore?

1115
01:31:18.003 --> 01:31:20.803
You don't have to achieve anything.

1116
01:31:22.003 --> 01:31:25.241
You just gotta have fucked up shit
happen to you.

1117
01:31:26.089 --> 01:31:29.384
So. you do have to die Sid.
Those are the rules.

1118
01:31:30.085 --> 01:31:32.285
New movie. new franchise.

1119
01:31:32.785 --> 01:31:35.214
There's only room for one lead
and let's face it.

1120
01:31:35.215 --> 01:31:38.184
your ingenue days.
they're over.

1121
01:31:44.475 --> 01:31:46.647
Don't tell me you didn't know
this day would come.

1122
01:33:06.758 --> 01:33:09.004
Oh. fuck!

1123
01:34:29.634 --> 01:34:31.005
Come on! Let's move in!

1124
01:34:41.291 --> 01:34:44.184
- Check the rooms. both sides and upstairs.
- Yes Ma'am.

1125
01:35:01.719 --> 01:35:03.904
- Jill. can you give us a description...
- Jill. over here...

1126
01:35:03.905 --> 01:35:05.205
Let's get outta here...

1127
01:35:18.006 --> 01:35:20.306
Jill. how does it feel to be a hero?...

1128
01:35:31.605 --> 01:35:35.788
Jill. You made it.
That's all that matters.

1129
01:35:36.389 --> 01:35:38.488
True. Charlie and Trev
tried to kill me.

1130
01:35:38.689 --> 01:35:43.757
And I heard they killed my mommy.
And Robbie and Kirby too.

1131
01:35:43.758 --> 01:35:47.240
Shhh. Just lay back.
Try to rest.

1132
01:35:49.175 --> 01:35:55.009
- Is... is your wife...
- She's gonna be fine... She's tough.

1133
01:35:56.820 --> 01:36:02.418
If I ever write a book one day. I want her
to write it with me. We'd be a good team.

1134
01:36:02.419 --> 01:36:05.252
with our...
matching wounds and all.

1135
01:36:08.173 --> 01:36:13.104
We're survivors now.
I just wish Sidney was too.

1136
01:36:14.105 --> 01:36:19.706
Jill... they're not sure yet.
It's still touch and go.

1137
01:36:20.697 --> 01:36:25.404
But she's in ICU and they think
Sidney just might make it.

1138
01:36:26.814 --> 01:36:30.829
What?
I mean. I saw Trevor kill her.

1139
01:36:30.830 --> 01:36:35.631
Look. we don't know yet.
But she's hanging on.

1140
01:36:38.654 --> 01:36:40.383
I... I wanted to see her.

1141
01:36:41.284 --> 01:36:46.315
She's not awake yet. And...
she may not remember anything.

1142
01:36:46.416 --> 01:36:47.716
You'll have to help her with that.

1143
01:36:49.123 --> 01:36:52.402
All in time.
Just get some rest now. okay?

1144
01:37:41.312 --> 01:37:46.588
- She gonna be okay?
- Yeah. she's a strong kid.

1145
01:37:46.689 --> 01:37:48.252
She's gonna have to be.

1146
01:37:48.653 --> 01:37:55.190
She asked if you were okay. She thinks
you guys should write a book together.

1147
01:37:55.191 --> 01:37:59.136
- With your matching wounds.
- Why. she was stabbed in the shoulder?

1148
01:38:03.334 --> 01:38:05.016
How did she know I was too?

1149
01:38:10.717 --> 01:38:11.717
Damn...

1150
01:38:17.912 --> 01:38:20.626
You just won't die. will you?

1151
01:38:22.227 --> 01:38:27.628
Who are you. Michael fucking Mayers?
Yeah. I don't think so.

1152
01:38:32.758 --> 01:38:34.654
Fucking die already!

1153
01:38:57.965 --> 01:38:59.678
How are those stitches?

1154
01:39:04.783 --> 01:39:05.800
<i>Sidney!</i>

1155
01:39:10.071 --> 01:39:12.944
- Hicks. get to the Sidney Prescott's
room and call for backup!

1156
01:39:12.945 --> 01:39:14.042
Be right up. Sir.

1157
01:39:22.313 --> 01:39:25.944
- Sid? Sid.
- Dewey!

1158
01:39:44.721 --> 01:39:48.988
Is this how it's gonna be. Sid? The ending
of the movie was supposed to be at

1159
01:39:48.989 --> 01:39:51.314
the house. I mean. this is just... silly.

1160
01:39:51.685 --> 01:39:56.898
Consider this an alternate ending. You're
not gonna get out of this. Jill.

1161
01:39:56.899 --> 01:39:58.478
- Of course I will.
- Dewey?

1162
01:40:00.309 --> 01:40:01.159
Sid...

1163
01:40:02.188 --> 01:40:06.348
Easy... Wait. wait.
What about the book?

1164
01:40:06.849 --> 01:40:08.949
Looks like.
I'll just have to write it myself.

1165
01:40:11.030 --> 01:40:12.222
Goddammit!

1166
01:40:14.398 --> 01:40:17.541
Don't even think about shooting
or I'll blow Dewey's head off.

1167
01:40:17.598 --> 01:40:19.914
What. you think I won't do it?
Give me your gun!

1168
01:40:21.515 --> 01:40:23.816
- Do it.
- You want her?

1169
01:40:32.292 --> 01:40:37.302
You just had to be the hero. huh?
Give me your gun.

1170
01:40:39.768 --> 01:40:44.266
What are you. deaf?
Give me... your gun.

1171
01:40:51.990 --> 01:40:53.039
And get up.

1172
01:40:55.540 --> 01:40:58.740
- And keep your hands over your head.
- Don't do anything stupi...

1173
01:41:00.486 --> 01:41:02.670
Don't fucking tell me what to do.

1174
01:41:03.250 --> 01:41:06.700
- Oh. God...
- Now. get up bitch.

1175
01:41:07.046 --> 01:41:11.904
- Okay.
- Get up. Now!

1176
01:41:11.905 --> 01:41:17.785
- Okay...
- She's not gonna help you. Come on.

1177
01:41:24.087 --> 01:41:27.488
Let's go.
Get your skinny ass out here.

1178
01:41:28.266 --> 01:41:33.775
- Okay...
- I'm gonna enjoy blowing your head off.

1179
01:41:34.699 --> 01:41:40.584
Okay. but can I just...
have one final word?

1180
01:41:40.985 --> 01:41:42.885
What? Please?

1181
01:41:45.252 --> 01:41:46.194
No...

1182
01:41:49.245 --> 01:41:51.241
- Clear.
- Clear?

1183
01:41:51.580 --> 01:41:52.555
Clear!

1184
01:41:58.089 --> 01:42:02.128
You forgot the first rule of remakes. Jill:
Don't fuck with the original.

1185
01:42:06.858 --> 01:42:10.657
- Oh my God. Dewey.
- Uh. what hit me?

1186
01:42:11.102 --> 01:42:15.912
Don't ask. You ok?

1187
01:42:19.068 --> 01:42:24.536
- She was standing right behind?
- They always are.

1188
01:42:37.328 --> 01:42:40.990
- Oh. God...
- Nice one.

1189
01:42:42.832 --> 01:42:49.104
- Hicks. you're alive?
- Wear the vest. save your chest.

1190
01:42:51.946 --> 01:42:57.799
I got two officers down.
several injuries and a new suspect.

1191
01:42:59.778 --> 01:43:02.252
We need a doctor. Goddammit!

1192
01:43:03.009 --> 01:43:05.454
I don't know about you.
but I feel a whole lot better.

1193
01:43:09.233 --> 01:43:11.830
<i>We're live at
Woodsboro Community Hospital.</i>

1194
01:43:11.831 --> 01:43:15.531
awaiting a first public statement
from Jill Roberts. survivor.

1195
01:43:15.532 --> 01:43:20.058
<i>A survivor of what is now being called
"the Woodsboro Massacre reboot"...</i>

1196
01:43:20.059 --> 01:43:23.646
<i>Jill Roberts is her name. A name
the whole world will now know...</i>

1197
01:43:23.647 --> 01:43:28.827
<i>who single-handedly put a stop to this
21st century Woodsboro killing spree...</i>

1198
01:43:28.828 --> 01:43:33.837
<i>Jill Roberts of Woodsboro. a girl
who's lifted all our spirits tonight.</i>

1199
01:43:33.838 --> 01:43:37.497
<i>An American hero.
right out of the movies.</i>
